verbs.description: In recent years , [ARG1: budget and staff] [V: cuts] [ARGM-LOC: at the Internal Revenue Service ( IRS )] meant less aggressive enforcement efforts , but a recent cash infusion may change that . In the new $ 1.3 trillion omnibus package that Congress passed and President Donald Trump signed into law , there was an additional $ 320 million for the Internal Revenue Service to implement the tax cuts approved last year . The money can be used to roll out taxpayer services and enforcement . In addition , $ 196 million was added to the agency 's annual budget . That could help with attrition at the IRS , which lost more than 6,800 staff positions over the past few years . The attrition had resulted in less aggressive enforcement .
